0x2aC782FeB46D4F750812ab17566b18a398A4E6B7

According to law, everyone who received $ETH has violated the sanctions and even now, anyone can send ETH to anyone. 

But any receiving address does not have a choice. 

Does that mean they all face legal action?
That would be very unethical.

13/

What about people who used tornado cash?

Many people have used tornado cash to donate to Ukraine, Afghanistan, and other causes before there were any sanctions.

After the sanction, someone sent 0.1E to many well-known accounts like Jimmy Fallon, Steve Aoki, Puma etc.

12/

This does not mean that sanctions can stop DeFi or any Dapp

Sanctions can impact token prices, slow down the growth of industry, user activity in the short term. But it cannot stop innovation

You can still interact with smart contracts, clone a front end, and use the app

11/

What about #Dapps?

They can face legal challenges and their front-end could be shut down

#Aave, #dydx, uniswap, balance, and many major Dapps are complying with OFAC, they have to. No founder wants to leave their family and go to jail

This is why pseudonymity is important

10/

Means that there is no way to sanction a tool, a robot, and you cannot treat it as a person; which is what OFAC did

This shows us flaws in technical and political systems

We need authorities who understand these technicalities so they can make better regulatory decisions

9/

In a way, the sanction is a blessing in disguise.

Infura and alchemy had to block RPC requests to tornado cash
Circle had to freeze $USDC, and Github suspended dev accounts

But you can still use it if you run an Ethereum node and now we know entities we need to decentralize

8/

Tornado Cash is code on the Ethereum blockchain, so no one, not even its creators or government, can effectively stop it

So technically, the sanction makes the use of Tornado cash illegal (doesn’t stop it) for US citizens. It will continue to operate everywhere else.

7/

The question remains, is it used more for good or bad?

Below is a breakdown by @chainalysis, which covers the use of tornado cash since its inception.

6/ https://t.co/0kxQngjAnS

5) Prevents backlash from an opposing community
6) Prevents employers who pay in crypto from seeing your on-chain activity
7) Prevents Dapps from getting all your on-chain activity

5/

Remember that all activity on the blockchain is public

1) Tornado cash allows many celebrities and smart individuals to hide their trading activity
2) Allows people to not lose opportunities they found
3) Allows famous people to not influence a project if they don’t want to

4/

Illegal applications for such a tool are easy to understand - money laundering, tax evasion, and redirecting funds from illegal activities.

However, there are many good use cases for Tornado cash. 
Here are some of them-

3/

Tornado Cash is a decentralized mixer that allows anyone to privately send money to anyone in the world.

Can criminals use it? Yes
Have they used it? Yes

Can it be used for good? Yes
Was it used for good? Yes

It’s a tool.

2/
